title: enterprising burglar
extract: enterprising. (entəʳpraɪzɪŋ ) adjective [usually ADJECTIVE noun] An enterprising person is willing to try out new, unusual ways of doing or achieving something. Some enterprising members found ways of reducing their expenses or raising their incomes.
